      "message": "Why is the default for timeout converted to a float?  \n\nget_capture could still be passed a timeout value that is an int and that argument will not be automatically coerced to a float during the call of the method.\n\ntimeout\u003d1 (or any int) should work since remaining_time will be coerced to a float on line 354.\n\nIf it does not work or if there is another reason for timeout to be a float, then line 316 should be\n  remaining_time \u003d float(timeout)",
      "range": {
